Demo mode 1: inside AWS
1. Start server
cd ~/Failover-UPF/SDN
sudo -E python3 sdn-server-inside-aws.py
2. Trigger
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/update-route-gnodeb \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "n3oldUPF": "192.168.40.11",
    "n3": [{"ip": "192.168.40.12"}],
    "n4": [{"ip": "192.168.50.12"}],
    "n6": [{"ip": "192.168.60.12"}]
  }'

Sửa IP theo UPF mới trong AWS của bạn.

3. Kiểm tra OVS flow
sudo ovs-ofctl -O OpenFlow13 dump-flows br-ovs | grep -E '192.168.40.11|192.168.40.12|2152|0x5101'
4. Bắt gói
sudo tcpdump -ni ens6 'udp port 2152'
sudo tcpdump -ni int0 'udp port 2152'
5. Cleanup
sudo ./cleanup_inside_aws.sh 192.168.40.12 192.168.40.11
Demo mode 2: cross-cloud AWS -> Azure
1. Start server
cd ~/Failover-UPF/SDN
sudo -E python3 sdn-server-cross-cloud.py
2. Trigger
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/update-route-gnodeb \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "n3oldUPF": "192.168.40.11",
    "n3": [{"ip": "10.60.41.4"}],
    "n4": [{"ip": "10.60.51.4"}],
    "n6": [{"ip": "10.60.61.4"}]
  }'
3. Kiểm tra route và NAT
ip route get 10.60.41.4

sudo iptables -t nat -S OUTPUT | grep upf-migrate-cross
sudo iptables -t nat -S INPUT | grep upf-migrate-cross || true

sudo ovs-ofctl -O OpenFlow13 dump-flows br-ovs | grep -E '192.168.40.11|10.60.41.4|2152' || true

Kỳ vọng route:

10.60.41.4 via 192.168.0.1 dev ens5 src 192.168.0.197
4. Bắt gói trên AWS

Mở 2 terminal:

sudo tcpdump -ni ens5 'host 10.60.41.4 and udp port 2152'
sudo tcpdump -ni ens6 'host 10.60.41.4 and udp port 2152'

Với mode cross-cloud, kỳ vọng packet đi ra ens5, không phải ens6.

5. Bắt gói trong Azure UPF pod
tcpdump -ni n3 'host 192.168.0.197 and udp port 2152'

Kỳ vọng thấy:

192.168.0.197.2152 > 10.60.41.4.2152 UDP
6. Test UE
ping -I uesimtun0 192.168.60.123

Nếu UPF nhận GTP-U rồi nhưng ping UE vẫn chưa thông, bước tiếp theo sẽ là debug UPF decap/N6/return route.

7. Cleanup
sudo ./cleanup_cross_cloud.sh 10.60.41.4 192.168.40.11
